<br />
Bards and rogues can spend 7aa now and have permanent illusions.  I know that it stays until clicked off, or you die.  What about if you log?
<br />

<br />
All of a sudden potions seem the way to go.  We drink a gnome potion, and if it stays when logged, you have just outdone the mask of the tinkerers and saved the 1 million platinim some want for this item.
<br />

<br />
1 backpack full of potions couild go such a long way.  Masks are now somewhat obsolete.
<br />

<br />
I mentioned to a dude in the bazaar who was selling a 1.2 million platinum mask (tinkerers one).  I warned him he might want to sell it sooner than later, because knowing Sony, they might either have a new drop with this illusion, or this new aa that could cast the illusion for maybe 5aa per race.  Guess 7aa is much better than the way I was speculating.
<br />

<br />
Would it be overpowering for a rogue and bard to have 1 potion last indefinite, while a warriors lasts one timed cast.  Bah it is only an illusion though.  Small bone for us.  (froglok stone is much more usefull now, use it click aa recharge it.)
<br />

