				<td colspan="2"><span>My OOW plans?
<br />

<br />
Well, I got my Mage, whom I retired 1.5 years ago and never touched again, to lvl 65, did some LDoNs to get a pet focus and bought him some equipment upgrades.
<br />

<br />
I really don't have the time or energy to level up another class, so I willhave to stick with 1 of 3 options:
<br />
- continue to play the Bard and suck the complete nerf of the class and accept I will never again have the powers I had at 65 because I am not -and will not be- in a guild that can get the lvl 69/70 songs in the next 2 years
<br />
- switch back to mage, to a class which in itself is bloody boring and underpowered, but at least will see a slight upgrade in OOW across the book.
<br />
- don't puchase OOW or retire from EQ ...well not purchasing OOW is as good as retiring.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Man, I so liked the Bard, but I just have nothing to look forward to.
<br />
I can realistically hope to get the lvl 66-68 songs in  half a year or so, when they are somewhat affordable.
<br />
But what is there?
<br />
- Some upgraded chants. woot.
<br />
- Some nerfed versions of echo of Trusik.  &quot;no sorry, necro...you don't get increase DoTs from me anymore as you are used to&quot;. &quot;no sorry dear Nuker, you get only 15% focus from me instead of 25%&quot;.
<br />
- A mezz that FINALLY again has only a 100-range (man, who needs that 200-range-crap anyway, heh?) and FINALLY brings back that annoying pushback.
<br />

<br />
For years to come I would feel like the gimped version of what I once was.
<br />

<br />
- So it's probably not byuing OOW for a while.
<br />
- Going back to play the extremly boring mage-class for some mindless nuking action.
<br />
- praying daily that something gets changed for Bards - for the better -
<br />

<br />
If only the lvl 69/70 spells/songs would be tradeable again, I had at least the outlook that I someday could do again what I can do now. But so?
<br />

<br />
*really frustrated*
<br />
